**Strategy pattern**: define a family of algorithms, encapsulate each, make them interchangeable.

```python
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Solver(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def solve(self, model):
        pass

class LPSolver(Solver):
    def solve(self, model): return linprog_solve(model)

class MILPSolver(Solver):
    def solve(self, model): return branch_and_bound(model)

class EnergyModel:
    def __init__(self, solver: Solver):
        self.solver = solver
    def optimize(self):
        return self.solver.solve(self)

# Swap solver without changing model code:
model = EnergyModel(solver=LPSolver())
model.solver = MILPSolver()  # upgrade without refactoring
```

MacroEnergy.jl uses this: swap between HiGHS, Gurobi, CPLEX without code changes.
